1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commemorate the two hundred nineteenth anniversary of Avoyelles Parish.
3 WHEREAS, established on March 31, 1807, Avoyelles Parish is one of the original
4 parishes of the Territory of Orleans which laid the foundation for a community whose
5 history stretches across more than two centuries; and
6 WHEREAS, the lands of Avoyelles were home to the indigenous Avoyel Tribe,
7 whose name the parish proudly carries, and later welcomed early French, Spanish, and
8 Acadian settlers who established farms, churches, and communities along the fertile banks
9 of Bayou des Glaises; and
10 WHEREAS, through generations of perseverance and faith, these early settlements
11 grew into the towns, villages, and rural communities that continue to define the character and
12 culture of Avoyelles Parish today; and
13 WHEREAS, the people of Avoyelles Parish contribute to the agricultural strength,
14 cultural traditions, and spiritual life that make Louisiana unique and preserve customs,
15 cuisine, music, and family traditions that reflect the parish's diverse heritage; and
16 WHEREAS, as Avoyelles Parish celebrates its two hundred nineteenth anniversary,
17 its citizens honor the legacy of those who came before while continuing to build a vibrant
18 future for generations yet to come.
19 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
20 commemorate the two hundred nineteenth anniversary of Avoyelles Parish and does hereby
